definition: having lost character, vitality, or strength
examples: the effete monarchies … of feudal Europe
… macrophages that recycle used iron from effete red cells.

definition: soft or delicate from or as if from a pampered existence, characteristic of an effete person
examples: peddled … trendy tweeds to effete Easterners
a wool scarf … a bit effete on an outdoorsman
a good-humored, effete boy brought up by maiden aunts
